A PDF containing all the notes so far can be found <a href="notes.pdf">here</a>. Comments, corrections and criticisms are most welcome!
      <h2> Resources and references:</h2>
      The main reference is <a href="https://services.math.duke.edu/~jgetz/aut_reps.pdf">Jayce Getz's notes</a>. Additionally, the following might be useful:
      <ul>
	<li> Bump's classic book <a href="https://typo.iwr.uni-heidelberg.de/fileadmin/groups/arithgeo/templates/data/Hauptseminare/Literature-WS13/bump-automorphic_forms_and_representations.pdf">Automorphic Forms and Representations</a>.</li>
	<li> Getz and Hahn's book <a href="https://sites.duke.edu/heekyounghahn/?page_id=117"> An Introduction to Automorphic Forms (...)</a>.</li>
	<li> Various notes references from <a href="https://users.ox.ac.uk/~kebl6248/LanglandsSeminar.html">George's seminar from last year</a> might be useful. </li>
      </ul>

